&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;King’s College Hospital NHS Foundation Trust part of King&#39;s Health Partners Academic Health Sciences Centre (AHSC), is one of the UK’s largest and busiest teaching hospitals with a turnover of nearly £1 billion, 1.5 million patient contacts a year and more than 12,600 staff based across 5 main sites in South East London and Kent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust provides a full range of local hospital services across its different sites, and specialist services from King’s College Hospital (KCH) site in Camberwell and the Princess Royal University Hospital (PRUH) site in Bromley, Orpington Hospital, and some services at Beckenham Beacon and Queen Mary’s Sidcup.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is recognised internationally for its work in liver disease and transplantation, neurosciences, cardiac, haemato-oncology, fetal medicine, stroke, major trauma, and Emergency Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The newly created post of Emergency Planning Officer at King’s College Hospital NHS Foundation Trust represents an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and highly motivated individual to join our Emergency Preparedness, Resilience and Response (EPRR) Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working closely with the Clinical Site Teams and Care Groups across the Trust, the post holder will support our two existing Emergency Planning Managers to ensure that emergency planning and resilience becomes an integral part of business as usual across the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to develop, produce and deliver training to all levels of staff across the Trust footprint. This training will include Emergency Response, Business Continuity and Chemical, Biological, Radiological and Nuclear (CBRN) packages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will also represent the Trust at external meetings and training events with other blue light services and local resilience organisations in the development of regional multi-agency response plans.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJon DaviesJob titleEmergency Planning ManagerEmail addressJon.davis@nhs.netTelephone number01698 863691Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jim Cook&lt;br /&gt;Emergency Planning Manager, King’s College Hospital&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 020 3299 7988&lt;br /&gt;james-v.cook@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
